        "headline": "USN-8018-2: Python regression",
        "content": {
          "excerpt_text": "USN-8018-1 fixed vulnerabilities in python3. That update introduced regressions. The patches for CVE-2025-15366 and CVE-2025-15367 caused behavior regressions in IMAP and POP3 handling, which upstream chose to avoid by not backporting them. Additionally, the patch for CVE-2026-0865 incorrectly rejected horizontal tabs in wsgiref headers. This update fixes these problems. We apologize for the inconvenience. Original advisory details: Denis Ledoux discovered that Python incorrectly parsed...",
          "lang": "en"
        },
